quran[27]{c,v,t,f}:
  56,94,"And burning in Hell-fire."
  56,95,"Verily, this! This is an absolute Truth with certainty."
  56,96,"So glorify with praises the Name of your Lord, the Most Great."
  68,28,"The best among them said: "
  68,29,"They said: "
  68,30,"Then they turned one against another, blaming."
  69,25,"But as for him who will be given his Record in his left hand, will say: "
  69,26,""
  69,27,""
  70,19,"Verily, man (disbeliever) was created very impatient;"
  70,20,"Irritable (discontented) when evil touches him;"
  70,21,"And niggardly when good touches him."
  71,16,"And has made the moon a light therein, and made the sun a lamp?"
  71,17,"And Allâh has brought you forth from the (dust of) earth? (Tafsir At-Tabarî)"
  71,18,"Afterwards He will return you into it (the earth), and bring you forth (again on the Day of Resurrection)?"
  72,13,"‘And indeed when we heard the Guidance (this Qur’ân), we believed therein (Islâmic Monotheism), and whosoever believes in his Lord shall have no fear, either of a decrease in the reward of his good deeds or an increase in the punishment for his sins."
  72,14,"‘And of us some are Muslims (who have submitted to Allâh, after listening to this Qur’ân), and of us some are Al-Qâsitûn (disbelievers - those who have deviated from the Right Path)’. And whosoever has embraced Islâm (i.e. has become a Muslim by submitting to Allâh), then such have sought the Right Path."
  72,15,"And as for the Qâsitûn (disbelievers who deviated from the Right Path), they shall be firewood for Hell,"
  73,7,"Verily, there is for you by day prolonged occupation with ordinary duties."
  73,8,"And remember the Name of your Lord and devote yourself to Him with a complete devotion."
  73,9,"(He Alone is) the Lord of the east and the west; Lâ ilâha illâ Huwa (none has the right to be worshipped but He). So take Him Alone as Wakîl (Disposer of your affairs).{1}",1:[{73:9} See the (Verse 3:173) and its footnotes.]
  74,4,"And purify your garments!"
  74,5,"And keep away from Ar-Rujz (the idols)!"
  74,6,"And give not a thing in order to have more (or consider not your deeds of obedience to Allâh as a favour to Him)."
  75,1,"I swear by the Day of Resurrection."
  75,2,"And I swear by the self-reproaching person (a believer)."
  75,3,"Does man (a disbeliever) think that We shall not assemble his bones?"